http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.
The most generic type of item.

An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
A description of the item.

A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See background notes for more details.
An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.
An associated logo.
The name of the item.
A photograph of this place.
URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.@value: UOMO (User Oriented social Media Ontology) Profile is an ontology for describing the information about Social Media focusing on the User's Profile.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/title.@value: UOMO (User Oriented social Media Ontology) Profile

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: Some socials have some goals that can be reached, and once it happens the achievement appears on a user profile
It is intended as a personalized features of some profiles that give the user the possibility to specifiy a place either with a link (uri) internal to the social media or just by typing it (string)
Also History
It is intended as the experiences of the user and also the skills of the user
In this particular kind of input box the communication is shared between possibly multiple users
Color palette is intended as the range of colors that can be applied to general elements of the profile such as texts, containers or the background.
It is intended as a section of a profile that gives some form of communication (not direct in the social) between the visitor of the profile and the person behind the user
A container is intended as a section of a profile that contains other elements such has media, hyperlinks, tags
The order through which the items in a container are displayed

With Highlighted Media it is meant the main media that is displayed in a part of the profile which is not the background or the profile pic. As an example we have the main video played when you enter a Youtube channel or the Twitch stream in a Twitch profile. Note that both these Social Media have a Profile Picture.
It is intended as a section of a profile that gives some form of communication (direct in the social) between the visitor of the profile and the user
It is intended as the information that some social display to see the date of the creation of the profile
It is intended as a container that aggregates some tags that represent particular interests of the user
Particular stats that is displayed on Reddit
More specific version of skill because it usually has a specific level
A Network Container is intended as a particular kind of container that aggregates other social media profile under specific relationships (such as "following", "followers" etc...)
The identifier of a user in a Social Media
This entity is used to describe the privacy settings of an entire profile or more in general to whichever social media data.
Numerical statistics linked to the profile
It is a more specific kind of working experience
It is intended as the information that some social media (like facebook) display on the profile as the answers of a set of predefined questions.
It's  a particular kind of achievement used in some socials for milestones.
UOMO (User Oriented social Media Ontology) Profile is an ontology for describing the information about Social Media focusing on the User's Profile.
It is intended as the structure and the content of a profile that belongs to a generic user (i.e. not Business Pages / account)
Some Social Media like Twitch or Youtube display the number of total views of the profile
It is a particular property of Twitch because the user can ban some emotes on her/his chat.
It is intended as the answer to a certain question in the "Trivia" section of a profile
It is intended both as the type of University or school general study program
It is used to categorize a certain experience or highlighted media
It is intended for every kind of educational certificates (School diploma or Proof)
It is intended as the grade obtained at the end of a particular educational experience

It is intended as the activities done during an educational experience that are not directly linked to the courses followed or grades obtained. (Example: Theatre Club, Nomination as the president of students or others...)
It is intended a particular biographic information that displays the favorite quotes of a user, all in string format
The field of the work done either by an organization or by the user in her/his working experience

With automatic it is meant that the container is generated automatically by inference of the Social Media itself (such as the "Comments" and "Post" containers of Reddit) and that the user cannot directly modify it (like you can in Facebook)
It is intended as the property of a chronological order because usually in social media the chronological order is from new to old, meanwhile usually it should start from the old and go to the new.
It is used to give a name to some social media elements
Particular data property applied to language competency that describes the competency level of that particular language
Different from uri because it's not always considered as an identificator
Some input content box have a cap of characters that you can type into them
It is intended as the question in the "Trivia" section of a profile
It applies to every social media data to specify if it is shareable or not.
It is used to specify, in the context of linking different social medias in a profile, if the social medias linked are represented also by an icon.
It is used for all the medias or personal experiences that may have a title
It can contain the general value of stats or contact info
